remarks: Component-setting is commutative when the x-values are different. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 5-Dec-2014.)  (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 30-Apr-2015.)
statement:
setscom.1 $e |- A e. _V $.
setscom.2 $e |- B e. _V $.
setscom $p |- ( ( ( S e. V /\ A =/= B ) /\ ( C e. W /\ D e. X ) ) -> ( ( S sSet <. A , C >. ) sSet <. B , D >. ) = ( ( S sSet <. B , D >. ) sSet <. A , C >. ) ) $.
